  "text": "Virtual screening libraries are often constructed from the application of common reactions to a set of seed molecules; the reactions are such that their products are predictable and easily performed in a laboratory setting while seed molecules are typically purchasable or easily synthesized or extracted from natural products. Even though the coverage of reactions tends to be a small subset of all possible reactions [CITATION_1] , the resulting combinations can lead to virtual libraries on the order of 10 14 − 10",
